Jack Prescott https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jack_Prescott 0 Jack Prescott (c.1880–?) was an early American silent film actor and director. Prescott starred in 19 films as an actor, between the end of 1914 and 1918, working with actors such as Charlotte Burton in films such as The Thoroughbred (1916). He also directed five short silent films in 1916 and retired from film in 1918. Prescott directed the films The Man Who Would Not Die and The Strength of Donald McKenzie in 1916.
